@startuml async-fill-flow
title FX-OEE — Order → Fill → Projection flow (async FillQueue + trade_events log)

skinparam sequenceMessageAlign center
skinparam maxMessageSize 220
actor Client
participant "OrderController\n(HTTP thread)" as HTTP
participant "MatchingService\n(engine, in-JVM)" as MS
queue "FillQueue\n(ConcurrentLinkedQueue)" as FQ
participant "PersistenceWorker\n(1 daemon thread)" as PW
database "trade_events\n(durable log)" as LOG
queue "Kafka\nTRADES_EXECUTED" as K
participant "FillConsumer\n(batched listener)" as FC
database "Postgres\n(DB projection)" as DB
participant "AccountState\n(in-mem mirror)" as MIRROR

== Hot path (per order) ==
Client -> HTTP : POST /orders
HTTP -> MS : submit(order)
activate MS
note right of MS
  Under per-pair book lock:
   1. validate (structural)
   2. reserve worst-case funds
   3. engine.match() → trades
   4. applyFills → ledger + positions
      (ENGINE = source of truth)
   5. reconcile locked margin
end note
MS -> FQ : enqueue(PendingFill)\n~1µs, wait-free
MS --> HTTP : ExecutionReport
deactivate MS
HTTP --> Client : 200 OK
note over MS, FQ #LightYellow
  Hot path NEVER blocks on Kafka.
  Ceiling lifts from ~200 ord/s (Kafka RTT)
  to CPU-bound.
end note

== Off hot path (worker thread) ==
PW -> FQ : drain(≤512)
activate PW
PW -> LOG : (1) appendBatch\nON CONFLICT(event_id) DO NOTHING
note right of LOG #LightGreen
  DURABLE COMMIT FIRST.
  This row is the single source
  both projections derive from.
end note
PW -> K : (2) publish TradeExecuted (sync ack)
PW -> LOG : (3) markPublished(event_ids)
PW -> K : (4) publish OrderMatched (async)
deactivate PW

== DB + mirror projection ==
K -> FC : onTradeBatch(List)
activate FC
FC -> MIRROR : applyAuthoritative(cashΔ, pnl, lotEvents)
FC -> DB : batched: deltas + lot opens/closes\n(dedup by tradeId:side)
deactivate FC

== Warm restart recovery ==
note over PW, FC #LightCyan
  On restart (fxoee.recovery.replay-on-startup=true):
   * engine rebuilt by replaying trade_events oldest-first
     (MatchingService.replayFill, via AccountBootstrapper)
   * relay re-publishes rows where published=FALSE
     → FillConsumer dedup (event_id) absorbs replay
  Crash BEFORE step 1  → order never committed; engine + DB agree it never happened.
  Crash AFTER  step 1  → relay re-publishes; DB catches up. NO DRIFT either way.
end note
@enduml
